trans-unit.source: Represents a variable-length stream of characters to be stored in or retrieved from the database.
To obtain an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleString> object, call the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOracleString%2A> method.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Data.OracleClient.OracleString"></xref> class and specifies the string to store.
The string to store.
Compares this instance of <xref href="System.Data.OracleClient.OracleString"></xref> to the supplied object and returns an indication of their relative values.
The object to be compared.
A signed number indicating the relative values of the instance and the object.
Return Value
Condition
Less than zero
This instance is less than object.
Zero
This instance is the same as object.
Greater than zero
This instance is greater than object
-or-

Gets the single byte from the `Value` property located at the position indicated by the integer parameter, index.
If `index` indicates a position beyond the end of the byte array, an exception is raised.
To avoid raising an exception, always check the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleString.IsNull%2A> property and the `Length` property before reading `this`.
This property is read-only.
